Class Argument

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nih.nlm.ling.sem.Argument

  • public class Argument
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a relation argument. An argument is basically a role/semantic item pair.
    Author:
    Halil Kilicoglu

      • getArgs

        public static java.util.List<Argument> getArgs​(java.util.List<Argument> args,
                                               java.lang.String name)
        Finds the arguments with a particular role.

        It allows approximate matches (e.g., ADJUNCT role will return ADJUNCT_TO, ADJUNCT_IN, etc.)

        Parameters:
        args - a list of arguments
        name - the role name
        Returns:
        arguments whose role begin with the name, null if the argument list is null

        Parameters:
        args - a list of arguments
        names - the array of role names
        Returns:
